SUMMARY:East Duwamish Work Party
DESCRIPTION:Join a restoration work party at East Duwamish GS: S Chicago St. \nHelp take care of the forest along this neighborhood trail! Depending on the time of the year\, we’ll be pulling and removing ivy\, cutting back and digging out blackberry or planting new plants; but always having a good time! \nThe forest is in South Beacon Hill/Rainier Beach. Use 8631 39th Ave S as an approximate address for the upper trail entrance\, where volunteers will meet.  \nOpen to the public\nAll ages OK \nLearn more + register here
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/east-duwamish-work-party-24/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/home-NEW-2-Catherine-Anstett-Trolls-Knoll-gloves.jpg
END:VEVENT
