UID:208267-1766829600-1766836800@www.seattleparksfoundation.org
SUMMARY:English Ivy Removal - Forest Fun for Everyone
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Kubota Gardens Natural Area. \nSo much ivy! Every month\, volunteers make a big difference by removing ivy so that trees\, bushes\, ferns and other native plants have room to grow. As you will quickly see\, the ivy covers large areas of ground and is climbing up trees. We also are discovering small Himalayan blackberry plants and getting those out immediately is a priority. No experience is needed – just bring your energy and interest in making a difference! \nLearn more + register
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/english-ivy-removal-forest-fun-for-everyone-6/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/home-NEW-2-Catherine-Anstett-Trolls-Knoll-gloves.jpg
END:VEVENT
